news.title: China Evergrande chairman's Hong Kong mansion seized by bank
news.para: The bank appointed receivers to take over the 5,000 sq ft (465 sq m) mansion on Nov. 1, according to a filing. Saddled with more than $300 billion in total liabilities, the defaulted Chinese property developer has already seen many of its assets, both in mainland China and Hong Kong, seized by creditors.

news.title: UK investors pull $208 million from property funds in October 2022
news.para: UK investors withdrew 184 million pounds ($207.66 million) from property funds in October, the biggest monthly outflows since June 2021, Calastone said.

news.title: Demolitions at 200 Raisina compounds only after GRAP-3 restrictions are lifted
news.para: Gurugram deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav said on Wednesday all illegal constructions in the area, identified by the Sohna Municipal Council on the NGT's directions in the same case in 2018, will be razed as soon as restrictions under the graded response action plan (GRAP) to check air pollution are removed.
